00026 /// \brief
00027 /// The FdoObjectType enumeration defines whether an object property is a single 
00028 /// value, a collection, or an ordered collection.
00029 /// <param name="FdoObjectType_Value">
00030 /// Represents a simple value property
00031 /// </param>
00032 /// <param name="FdoObjectType_Collection">
00033 /// Represents a property that is a collection of values
00034 /// </param>
00035 /// <param name="FdoObjectType_OrderedCollection">
00036 /// Represents a property that is an ordered collection of values
00037 /// </param>
00038 enum FdoObjectType
00039 {
00040     /// Represents a simple value property.
00041     FdoObjectType_Value,
00042 
00043     /// Represents a property that is a collection of values.
00044     FdoObjectType_Collection,
00045 
00046     /// Represents a property that is an ordered collection of values.
00047     FdoObjectType_OrderedCollection
00048 };
00049 #endif
